&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); color:rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family:calibri,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt; Lisa Dungan Roth, 503-913-6529 or lroth@pps.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On Saturday, November 1, 2025, at approximately 12:00 p.m., Tualatin Police officers responded to a report of a body in the water at the Lake of the Commons, located at 8325 SW Nyberg Street in Tualatin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upon arrival, responders located and recovered a deceased male, identified as Gary Schott, 69, of Oregon City.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Preliminary findings indicate no signs of foul play. The Washington County Medical Examiner&rsquo;s Office is conducting an investigation to determine the cause and manner of death.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Tualatin Police Department extends its condolences to Mr. Schott&rsquo;s family and loved ones.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nov. 3, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

